{
  "stem": "13690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I can give you one advice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On the other corner of the cellar, there is a barrel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Be careful.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "On the top of the barrel there's a sauerkraut-- it's cabbage there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there's a big stone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If you could push a little bit-- don't push the stone-- if you could push your small and skinny arm, maybe you could get out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there was a big barrel there with cabbage, and I put my little arm in there and I managed to get out a little bit of--",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strands of cabbage.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was sour.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I gave it to my sister and she says, oh, that's so good.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's so delicious, so good.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we stayed there quite a few hours, and seemingly, that my mother's supposed to come to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he went back instead.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The same man.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the same man, expecting that mother's coming back, he brought back a letter from my father and he said, my dear children, I want you back.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I want you dearly back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Go and listen to that man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's going to take you back to town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew that we won't be able to walk.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He said, no, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Your father paid enough money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I hired a sled with horses.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was high snow, very big snow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had a sled with horses and he took us back into the town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I said, but where will you take us?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know where my father-- He said, no, your father said-- at daybreak he will be waiting at the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father, there, standing in subfreezing weather, waiting-- not knowing exactly the time and hour when the two poor children would come.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was waiting, and he embraced us and he was crying and he took us back.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
